            <div class="panel radius">

              <h4>Mission Statement</h4>
              <!-- <div class="landing-img" id="site-title"></div> -->
              <p>Over 100,000 Byzantine seals are housed in a wide array of collections,
               many of which are only partially published or presented across scattered books,
               articles or platforms. For the first time, this Portal offers a unified entry point,
               allowing these dispersed holdings to be comprehensively searched—and unlocking new avenues for research.</p>

              <p>The lack of publicly accessible information on seals has long been a major gap in Byzantine sigillography.
               This initiative responds to that need by offering a user-friendly and pragmatic platform for sharing data,
                with minimal requirements for participation.</p>

              <p>Every seal description remains clearly credited to its respective contributor,
               who retains full responsibility for the content.</p>

               <p>With CSÆB, you can search a metacorpus comprising potentially tens of thousands of seals from various collections—all in a single click.</p>
            </div>
